		{"id":"936193ff50840038","type":"text","text":"Game idea: \n\nyou have basic questions: why, who, how.\n\nEnemies: are emotions/thoughts -> usually in couples and you keep looping between them until you gain a certain clarity stat\n\nOr you fight each emotion until you reach a certain clarity and then go on to the next one. each time you use all your cards without reaching that clarity point -> all your cards are gone but you keep one and restart\n\nlevel 1) guilt and grief. Level 2) anger and shame\n\nasking the enemies questions triggers their attacks but gives player memory/support cards.\n\nquestions can be asked to the enemy only a set number of times and then the button gets greyed out.\n\nreaching 0 sanity = loss, reaching 100 clarity (by beating boss) = win\n\n","x":820,"y":402,"width":638,"height":535},
